        "subject": "LU-19980 build: improve lock_manager_operations tests",
        "message": "LU-19980 build: improve lock_manager_operations tests\n\nConfigure tests that use \"struct lock_manager_operations\" will\nfail after:\n\nLinux commit v6.2-rc3-9-g5970e15dbcfe\n  filelock: move file locking definitions to separate header file\n\nRun the configure test LC_HAVE_LOCKS_LOCK_FILE_WAIT_IN_FILELOCK\nearly so the resulting HAVE_LINUX_FILELOCK_HEADER is available\nfor \"struct lock_manager_operations\" tests to conditionally\n\n  #include <linux/filelock.h>\n\nHPE-bug-id: LUS-13279\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Shaun Tancheff <shaun.tancheff@hpe.com>\nChange-Id: I95b66bb27aa6b32c5803f4fb285c7529e551b909\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/64541\nReviewed-by: Andriy Skulysh <andriy.skulysh@hpe.com>\nReviewed-by: Rajeev Mishra <rajeevm@hpe.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Nikitas Angelinas <nikitas.angelinas@hpe.com>\nReviewed-by: Timothy Day <timday@thelustrecollective.com>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
